{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Review input is limited to changed lines (diff hunks), not full modified-file contents.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is usually in wiring between diff extraction, file-loading, and prompt/input construction. A unit test on one parser function can pass while end-to-end assembly still leaks unchanged lines; no real external API is strictly required to catch that class.","test_description":"Build an integration test that feeds a realistic unified diff plus full-file contents through the real review-input builder modules, then assert the final model input contains only changed hunks (and required small context) and excludes unchanged regions from the modified files.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are posted at correct diff-view positions on the PR.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics (path, side, line/start_line or position mapping). In-process mocks often accept invalid mappings that GitHub rejects or repositions.","test_description":"Run against a real test PR in a staging repository: post inline comments using the production comment-posting path, then fetch PR review comments from GitHub and verify each expected file/line maps to the intended changed line in the diff view.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Agent finds at least one real defect in a PR containing a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model judgment quality, not just deterministic plumbing. Mocking the model would hide the core failure (missing the bug).","test_description":"Use a benchmark PR fixture with a deliberately introduced bug and run the real model call through the review flow. Assert at least one finding correctly targets the known defect (by file/line and defect type rubric). Execute multiple trials and require a minimum hit rate to account for non-determinism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every summary finding has a matching inline comment; no orphan findings in top-level summary.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily a consistency invariant across internal data structures and posting results (finding IDs, file/line refs, posted-comment IDs). Unit tests can miss cross-module mismatches.","test_description":"Run the real summarization/composition and posting-orchestration modules with a multi-finding review result and captured inline-post responses. Assert summary entries are generated only from successfully posted inline findings and each summary item maps 1:1 to an inline comment reference.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Full unattended sequence on a real PR: read diff, post inline comments, then post summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This validates the full agent pipeline across sequential steps with shared state and side effects. Real failures emerge from step ordering, retries, cross-step state propagation, and real service interactions; a lower-level test can miss these pipeline-level breakdowns.","test_description":"Execute an end-to-end run on a real staging PR with the production trigger path. Verify completion without manual actions, confirm inline comments were created first, then confirm a top-level summary comment was posted that reflects the posted inline findings. Include timeout/retry expectations and assert terminal success state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.32,"Agentic":0.23,"Workflow":0.35}}]}
